'''Sir Richard Eyre Cox, 4th Baronet''' was an Irish baronet.<ref>[https://archive.org/stream/cu31924092524408#page/n257/mode/2up Complete Baronetage]</ref>

He was the  son of [[Venerable|The Ven.]] [[Sir Michael Cox, 3rd Baronet]],<ref>"Alumni Dublinenses : a register of the students, graduates, professors and provosts of Trinity College in the University of Dublin (1593-1860)" Burtchaell, George Dames/Sadleir, Thomas Ulick (Eds) p185:  Dublin, Alex Thom and Co, 1935</ref>[[Archdeacon of Cashel]] from 1767 to 1772,  and his wife Elizabeth Massy, daughter of [[Hugh Massy, 1st Baron Massy]], and widow of John Arthur.  He  married Mary O'Brien, great granddaughter of [[William O'Brien, 3rd Earl of Inchiquin]]. He was drowned on 17 September 1783.<ref>[http://www.thepeerage.com/p25300.htm#i252994 thePeerage.com]</ref> His widow remarried [[William Saurin]], for many years the [[Attorney General for Ireland]], by whom she had at least four children. She died in 1840.

